Privacy Policy
Updated December 2024
1. About Medal.tv
We are Medal B.V. (trading under the name
Medal.tv
). We offer an online platform (the Platform) for recording, watching, and sharing gameplay clips and videos (together
Clips
), and access the best-shared content by the gaming community within a safe and friendly environment. We enable users to interact with each other through clips, likes, voice chat and messages. The use of the Platform and all related services thereto hereinafter referred to as: the
Services
. These Services are accessible via https://medal.tv (the
Website
), via the Medal.tv desktop software (the
Desktop App
) and via the Medal.tv iOS and Android applications (the
Mobile Apps
).
2. What is this?
This is a
Privacy Policy
. In this document we explain what type of personal data we collect when you use our Services, when you visit our Website, or when you apply for our
open roles
. We also explain for what purposes we use the data, how we secure them and how we store them.
3. Privacy and Privacy Legislation
Personal Data
means all information by which a person can be directly or indirectly identified. We process your Personal Data in line with the General Data Protection Regulation (
GDPR
), California Consumer Privacy Act (
CCPA
), and other relevant legislation on the protection of Personal Data (collectively referred to as the
Privacy Legislation
).
4. Our role as (Joint) Controller
We collect and process the Personal Data in the context of our Services. We determine the purposes and means of these processing activities. This means we act as
Controller
within the meaning of the Privacy Legislation.
Next to that, there are specific processing activities for which we act as joint Controller. These processing activities are mentioned under paragraph 7.
5. What Personal Data are processed by Medal.tv, why and on what basis?
As Controller we may process your (personal) data if you use our Services, and/or when you visit our Website and/or social media pages.
When you use our Services through the Website, Desktop App and/or Mobile App
If you create an account:
Username, email address, password, year of birth.
Optional: uploaded biography, phone number, donation link, your profile photo.
Non-personal: the details of the hardware you are using.
Please note: if you choose to log in via third party account(s) or to connect your account with such third party account, you authorize us (through OAuth) to process your Personal Data linked to this account (such as your username, real name, email address, profile picture, friends or followers – depending on the third party and which data you share with them).
We may use these data to:
Register your account
Enable you to access your account and our Services
Allow us to communicate with you and approach you appropriately in our communications
Send you notifications and service updates related to your use of our Services
Flag, report and prevent misuse, fraud and threats of/regarding to our Services.
Improve our services.
We may process these data, because this is necessary to
perform our contract
with you (i.e. to provide our Services).
We may send you service updates based on our legitimate interest to keep you informed about activities related to your use of our Services. It is always possible to unsubscribe from our service updates via the link at the bottom of each service update.
We may send you notifications if you gave us permission to do so. It is always possible to opt-out from these notifications via the settings of your device.
We may also process (some of) these data because we have a
legitimate interest
to ensure a secure use of the Accounts and associated Services.
We may process your year of birth because we have a legitimate interest to you such information to get a better understanding of the use of our Services.
We may process your hardware information based on a legitimate interest in understanding what hardware is most popular among our users, to understand crashes and bugs in our software, and optimize the service for your hardware.
We will carry out audio scanning and moderation of the Clips in accordance with our legal obligations (including under the Digital Services Act) and pursuant to our legitimate business interest to protect users from and to remove harmful and unlawful content from our Platform.
If you post contest-hashtags within the context of game contests, we may share the Personal Data included in this post with the relevant game studio because we have your permission to do so (i.e., by you posting your content accompanied with the indicated contest hashtag). Please check the privacy notice of the relevant game studio to see how your Personal Data are handled. Game studios we partner with are indicated along with the announcement of the contest hashtag.
If you use our Find you Friends functionality in order to find friends already on Medal, to invite your contacts to start using Medal and to be found by your friends already on Medal:
The names and respective contact information included in your contact list (in hashed form).
If you are an existing user of Medal, your username and other information included in your Account.
Please note:
Medal does not process personal data of individuals in the contact list, as Medal cannot reverse the hashing of this data.
We use these data to:
Show you which of your contacts use Medal and to make it easy to connect with these friends;
Facilitate you in inviting new friends to Medal. Such invitation will then be sent via your own SMS/Messenger app.
We may process the personal data included in your contact list because we have
your permission
to do so.
Besides that, we may show existing friends on Medal in providing the ‘Find your Friends’ functionality because we have a
legitimate interest
to provide such functionality.
Medal designed this functionality in a privacy friendly way, as it has implemented additional safeguards to limit the impact on the privacy of our users, namely by hashing the personal data obtained from the contact list and by clearly informing you about this functionality via this privacy notice.
If you use our desktop app while playing games:
The game you are playing, for some games also your in-game identifiers (username/tagline and unique identifier), and for some games the match, map, region or server you are in.
We use these data to:
Show other Medal users stats about the match clips are taken from and connect you to other Medal users you are playing with.
We process this data based on
legitimate interest
in providing you a better service where you can connect with the people you play with.
If you choose Connect Mobile:
Phone number
We use these data to:
Connect your account with the Mobile App on your phone.
We may process these data, because this is necessary to
perform our contract
with you (i.e. to execute the requested Service).
If you upload, download and/or share content:
The content you make available on the Platform, such as: your username, email address, comments, likes, posts, chats with other users and/or any uploaded Clips with or without accompanying audio; and your phone number, if you request to download a Clip via a link by text; and Metadata associated with public uploads
In relation to in-game content uploaded by you, we may also capture the input controls you use to play the game (In-game Controls).
We may use these data to:
Allow you to view, download and upload Clips on our Platform;
Allow you to use all related Services thereto;
Allow you to communicate with other users through likes, comments, posts and chats;
Enable you to share your Medal content on your other online profiles according to your preferences; and share your public Medal content (including through our API) on the platforms or websites of our partners, such as game studios and other platforms like Xbox (Microsoft);
Create controller and keyboard overlays, which can be added to your clips;
Do research on and create data algorithms, AI algorithms, or data-based features;
We may also use the data to provide and maintain the platform, and to continue to deliver quality product generally to users. Data can be used to improve the quality of data algorithms, which are used in the product or by the company.
Carry out audio scanning of the Clips for the purpose of identifying and moderating illegal activity and harmful behaviour and ensuring compliance with Medal’s codes of conduct.
We may process these data, because this is necessary to
perform our contract
with you (i.e. to provide our Services).
If you post contest-hashtags within the context of game contests, we may share the Personal Data included in this post with the relevant game studio because we have
your permission
to do so (i.e., by you posting your content accompanied with the indicated contest hashtag). Please check the privacy notice of the relevant game studio to see how your Personal Data is handled. Game studios we partner with are indicated along with the announcement of the contest hashtag.
Users may opt-out of the collection or usage of this data in the privacy section of the in-app settings.
If you subscribe to our newsletters
Your email address
We use these data to:
Send you messages about promotions, (new) features and/or products on our Platform and all our related Services.
We may send you these e-mails if you gave us
permission
to do so.
It is always possible to unsubscribe from these e-mails via the link at the bottom of each e-mail.
If you create a support ticket
Your username, email address, the Discord name (optional), and the content of the correspondence between you and Medal.tv.
We use these data to:
Answer your questions and/or handle any complaints; and
Improve our Services as a result of questions and feedback from you.
We may process these data, because we have a
legitimate interest
to contact and assist you based on your comment or question and to improve our Services as a result of the questions and feedback we receive.
Technical information
IP-address, your country, (selected) language, usage behaviour of our Services and your unique device identifier.
We use these data to:
Analyse the use of our Services;
Improve our Services;
Improve the security of the Platform, Services, and accounts; and
Flag, report and prevent misuse, fraud and threats of/regarding to our Services.
We may process these data because we have a
legitimate interest
to gain insight in the use of our Platform for the sake of improving our Services.
User Testing
Contact information such as Discord username, to assess whether you qualify to participate in our user testing program.
Age, location, username, type of games you usually play, whether you are a member of any of our (early access) communities, and a recording of the screen share, in case you participate in our user testing program.
We use this data to:
Assess your eligibility to participate in our user testing program;
Establish a good rapport at the beginning of the (chat)conversation;
Conduct the survey; and
Improve our Services.
We may process these data to assess whether you qualify to participate in our user testing program, because we have a
legitimate interest
in selecting a group of users eligible for our user testing program and because you have opted in to be a 'early access' user and/or because you have subscribed to dedicated 'user testing' channels.
In case you participate in our user testing program, we ask for your
permission
for all other processing of Personal Data required for the user testing.
If you accept targeted advertising, tracking cookies and analytics and usage behaviour data from the use of our Services. This may include the following:
Hardware specifications;
Your system language;
Your country based on IP address;
Estimated age or given age based on surveys run within Medal’s ecosystem;
Installed games and services on your device;
Clips captured, games played, session count, and session time from games and their associated servers, mods, or subgame/experience ie which specific Roblox game while Medal’s applications are running;
On platform content consumption data including game watched, number of clips watched, total watch time, sharing, and other consumption metrics.
We use this data to:
Deliver relevant website content and targeted advertisements to you based on one or more criteria from the data we collect; and
Measure or understand the effectiveness of the advertising we serve to you.
We may process your personal data to provide you with targeted advertising because we have
your consent
to do so.
It is always possible to opt-out of any such use of your personal data for targeted advertising purposes by withdrawing your consent for the use of tracking cookie(s) in accordance with our cookie statement.
When you visit our social media pages
Uploaded information
Information of visitors who leave a comment or otherwise post something on our social media pages, including the Personal Data contained within these comments and/or posts.
We use these data to:
Contact the visitors in reply of their post and/or comment via our social media pages; and
Process the feedback left on our social media pages.
We may process these data, because we have a
legitimate interest
to process these data and because the visitors voluntarily made public such information.
Our social media pages are also controlled by the social medium itself. Please check their own privacy policies, to see how each social medium handles Personal Data, among which:
