When you apply for our open roles:
Personal Data:
Purpose(s):
Legal ground(s):
Contact details
First name and surname, e-mail address, address and telephone number.
We use these data to contact you about the application.
We may process these data, because we have a
legitimate interest
in processing these data. We need the data to get (and keep) in touch with you and to process and review the application.
Application Information
Information provided by you, among others: Personal Data included in the Curriculum Vitae and motivation letter, qualifications, photo, gender and day of birth.
We use these data to:
assess whether you suit the job and Medal; and
determine who is the most suitable candidate.
We may process these data, because we have a
legitimate interest
in processing these data and because you provide this data yourself and voluntarily. We need the data to get (and keep) in touch with you and to process and review the application.
Information retained during application process
Notes from interviews.
We use these data to:
assess whether you suit the job at Medal; and
determine who is the most suitable candidate.
We may process these data, because we have a
legitimate interest
in processing these data and because you provide this data yourself and voluntarily. We need the data to get (and keep) in touch with you and to process and review the application.
Information from public sources
Information in public profiles, such as LinkedIn and other social networks (where applicable).
We use these data to:
assess whether you suit the job at Medal; and
determine who is the most suitable candidate.
We have a
legitimate interest
to process these data as we need them to process and assess the application.
We only process information that is relevant for the application and you always get the opportunity to react to our findings.
6. How long do we keep the Personal Data?
We store Personal Data for as long as we need it for the above purposes. In this respect, we apply the following retention periods:
Personal Data of the users of our Services
| This data is stored as long as the user has an active account on our Platform and for a maximum period of 24 months after the last use of our Platform. We delete your Personal Data earlier if you delete your account yourself. In that case, we delete your Personal Data 14 days after deletion of the account.
Personal data processed via Access the Phone List functionality
| This data is stored as long as necessary to perform this functionality or until the consent is withdrawn.
Personal Data of Website visitors
| This data is stored as long as it is necessary to provide the Services you as a user have requested.
Personal Data in our correspondence
| This data is stored as long as necessary to handle your message/question/complaint.
Personal Data of job applicants
| This data is stored for a maximum of 4 weeks after the application process is finalized and/or when the procedure with the specific applicant ends, unless you gave us permission to store the Personal Data for (up to) 1 year to re-engage you in alternative procedures.
Other information
| We store other Personal Data only for as long as it is necessary for the purposes. This is deleted as soon as it is no longer necessary for the purposes for which we processed it or, if applicable, the consent for such processing is withdrawn.
After expiry of the retention periods, we may process and retain certain Personal Data to comply with legal retention obligations and/or for fraud/misuse investigations/possible legal proceedings. In such events, we will retain the data separately and only use such data for the aforementioned purposes.
7. Do we share your Personal Data with others?
Processors
We use the services of Processors for the processing of (personal) data. Within this context these Processors receive Personal Data from us which they process on our behalf. We use, for instance, processors for hosting our Platform, managing our CRM, and monitoring and analyzing the safety and use of our Services.
The Processors must strictly follow our instructions regarding the processing of such Personal Data. Therefore, they will not use the Personal Data for their own purposes. We will ensure that all Processors comply with the requirements of the Privacy Legislation. Joint Controllers
Where Medal and another entity jointly determine the purposes and means of processing, Medal acts with such other party as joint controller within the meaning of the GDPR. In that case, the parties involved have defined their respective responsibilities, roles, and relationships in a mutual arrangement.
The following parties are acting as joint controllers with Medal:
Entities within the Medal group
| Regarding the processing activities as set out in the table above, Medal involves other companies within its group. Medal is the first point of contact executing for your rights as described in this Privacy Notice in relation to the Personal Data processed within this joint relationship.
Where appropriate, Medal (or the other joint controller) may refer you to the other party, if you can exercise your rights more quickly or effectively with the other party.
External Controllers
We may also share your Personal Data with external controllers in the following cases:
Payments:
Your Payment will be processed via a third-party payment service provider (including but not limited to iDeal, VISA, PayPal, MasterCard, Paddle, Stripe and PayPal) and respectively the terms and conditions of those services will apply to the payments you make using the respective third-party. Any Personal Data you provide to this payment provider will be processed by the payment provider (as Data Controller) in accordance with their own privacy policies.
Tax authorities:
We are legally obliged to include (some of) the Personal Data in our financial administration, which may have to be shared with various national tax authorities. The tax authorities will process these Personal Data in accordance with its own privacy policies.
Game Studios
: We may share Personal Data with our partners such as game studios after you gave your permission to do so (i.e. by you posting your content accompanied with the indicated contest hashtag). For more information on how these parties (as Controller) process your Personal Data, please refer to their privacy notice, as provided along with the contest hashtag.
Technology operators:
Public clips and associated metadata may be shared with third parties as they are in the public sphere to facilitate the creation of data algorithms, data- based features, or AI algorithms.
Apart from the above, we may share your Personal Data with third parties if we are legally obliged to do so. The CCPA enables consumers to opt-out of sharing of their personal information to third parties, which can be done in the privacy section of the app settings.
8. Cookies
We may use cookies on our Website. A cookie is a simple small text file that can be stored in your computer when visiting the Website. This text file identifies your browser and/or computer. When visiting our Website again, the cookie ensures that our Website recognizes your browser or computer.
For more information on our use of cookies, please refer to our
cookie statement
.
9. Our Recommender Systems
The Medal recommendation system is a heuristic and machine driven system which allows users to view only content which has been marked as public and viewable by other users. The system works by applying an algorithm to a small set of pre-determined content features which allows us to rank such content for our users. Those features include:
the game the content was captured from;
the time it was captured;
the number of shares, likes and views it has aggregated over time;
the number of comments, replies, and upvotes it has aggregated over time
whether the content went through an editing flow.
These features are then matched by our algorithm to a user’s individual characteristics based on their prior preferences and history of usage, in particular: (a) Medal content that they have watched, liked, shared, or commented on inside of our platform, and (b) interactions from a user’s followed network on that piece of Medal content in order to deliver the particular recommendations each user receives.
Our recommendation system operates in full compliance with all applicable laws and regulations, including as to data protection.
10. hCaptcha
We use the hCaptcha anti-bot service (hereinafter "hCaptcha") on our website. This service is provided by Intuition Machines, Inc., a Delaware US Corporation ("IMI"). hCaptcha is used to check whether the data entered on our website (such as on a login page or contact form) has been entered by a human or by an automated program. To do this, hCaptcha analyzes the behavior of the website or mobile app visitor based on various characteristics. This analysis starts automatically as soon as the website or mobile app visitor enters a part of the website or app with hCaptcha enabled. For the analysis, hCaptcha evaluates various information (e.g. IP address, how long the visitor has been on the website or app, or mouse movements made by the user). The data collected during the analysis will be forwarded to IMI. hCaptcha analysis in the "invisible mode" may take place completely in the background. Website or app visitors are not advised that such an analysis is taking place if the user is not shown a challenge. Data processing is based on Art. 6(1)(f) of the GDPR (DSGVO): the website or mobile app operator has a legitimate interest in protecting its site from abusive automated crawling and spam. IMI acts as a "data processor" acting on behalf of its customers as defined under the GDPR, and a "service provider" for the purposes of the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). For more information about hCaptcha and IMI's privacy policy and terms of use, please visit the following links:
https://www.hcaptcha.com/privacy
and
https://www.hcaptcha.com/terms
.
11. Is your data transferred outside the European Economic Area (EEA)?
We may transfer Personal Data to parties outside the EU, if one of our third parties is established outside the EU. We make sure the transmission of Personal Data outside the EU is in accordance with the Privacy Legislation (chapter 5 of the GDPR), meaning the Personal Data will only be transferred to a company or country that provides an adequate level of protection.
12. Third party websites
You may find advertising or other (hyper)links on our Platform that link to the websites, products and services of partners, suppliers, advertisers, sponsors, licensors or other third parties. We do not control the content or the links that appear on these websites and we are not responsible for the practices employed by websites linked to or from our Platform. In addition, these websites, products, and services, including their content and links, may be constantly changing. These websites, products and services may have their own privacy policies, user terms and customer service policies. Browsing and interaction on any other website, including websites that are linked to or from our Platform, are subject to the terms and policies of that website.
13. Changes in this Privacy Policy
We are constantly looking for ways to improve our Website and Services. Therefore, we may update this Privacy Notice from time to time. If we change the Privacy Notice significantly, we will post a notification on our Website together with the updated Privacy Notice.
14. How do we protect the Personal Data?
We take appropriate organizational and technical measures to protect personal data against loss or other forms of unlawful processing. These measures ensure a level of security that is appropriate to the data we process.
15. Your rights and who to contact
As laid down in the Privacy Legislation, you have the right to:
Ask us for access to and/or a copy of the Personal Data we process of you;
Ask us to transfer such copy to another data controller;
Ask us to adjust, review or remove your Personal Data from our systems;
Ask us to restrict the processing of your Personal Data;
Object to the processing of your Personal Data;
Withdraw your permission (without consequences for the Personal Data that was processed before your withdrawal); and
File a complaint with the Dutch Data Protection Authority, if you believe that we process your Personal Data unlawfully.
If you have any questions, comments or concerns regarding the way we handle your Personal Data, please contact our Data Protection Officer via
privacy@medal.tv
16. Contact Information
